sect1.para:
        You can also listen logging events generated by Hazelcast runtime by registeringLogListeners
        toLoggingService.

LogListener listener = new LogListener() {
    public void log(LogEvent logEvent) {
        // do something
    }
}
LoggingService loggingService = Hazelcast.getLoggingService();
loggingService.addLogListener(Level.INFO, listener):

        Through the
        LoggingService
        you can get the current used ILogger implementation and log your own messages too.
